revision.text:
[[File:Aat de Peijper.jpg|thumbnail|Aat de Peijper]] '''Adriaan "Aat" de Peijper''' (died 1998)<ref name=kas>Jan Kas, [http://www.refdag.nl/nieuws/binnenland/kostbare_postzegel_met_nijkerkse_stempel_geveild_voor_16_000_euro_1_823253 Kostbare postzegel met Nijkerkse stempel geveild voor 16.000 euro], Reformatisch Dagblad, 28 April 2004. {{nl}}</ref> was a Dutch industrialist and [[philatelist]] whose collection of Dutch, Dutch colonial, and British Commonwealth stamps included several world rarities.
==Career== Until 1976 De Peijper was director of a pharmaceutical distribution company in [[Etten-Leur]].<ref name=kas/> De Peijper and his company Centrafarm won a number of court battles concerning their redistribution of medicines within the EU,<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=WkCjxAXZFDsC&pg=PA17 Weer kort geding tegen geneesmiddelenimporteur], Nieuwe Leidsche Courant, 26 August 1976. {{nl}}</ref> including some against [[Sterling Drug]] / Winthrop that are considered landmark cases.<ref>Floris O.W. Vogelaar, [https://books.google.com/books?id=WkCjxAXZFDsC&pg=PA17 The EU Competition Rules: Landmark Cases of the EU Courts and the European Commission], pp. 17-19</ref><ref>[http://lesnouvelles.lesi.org/lesnouvelles1974/lesNouvellesPDF12-74/Landmark-Decision-by-EC-Court.pdf Landmark Decision by EC Court]</ref> <!-- In principal, the Adriaan de Peijper in the court cases could be a cousin in the same business, but the fact that the stamp collector was director of a pharmaceutical company in Etten-Leur (Centrafarm is currently based in Etten-Leur) and that the collector retired in 1976 (after Adriaan de Peijper and Centrafarm won the last court case) seems to support this link. -->
==Philately== De Peijper began collecting stamps from a young age but according to his wife Mrs M.W. de Peijper-Pieksma, it was not until later in life that he was able to afford the more expensive items missing from his collection. He bought many items from the Samos collection, and also items formerly in the [[John Robert Boker, Jr.|Boker]], [[Maurice Burrus|Burrus]], [[Alfred H. Caspary|Casapry]], and [[Louise Boyd Dale|Dale-Lichtenstein]] collections.<ref name=collection>''The Collection Aat de Peijper''. De Nederlandsche Postzegelveiling, Amsterdam, 2013. pp. 4-5.</ref>
His collection was principally of the stamps of the Netherlands, with a focus on the first issue,<ref>[http://www.vandieten.nl/catalogus_629/ Auction catalogue Netherlands collection Aat de Peijper, part II]</ref> the British Commonwealth and Dutch colonies. Among the rarities in the collection was a 1925 Kenya and Uganda £100 (SG105) unused [[plate number]] postage stamp (signed A. Diena in the margin),<ref>''The Collection Aat de Peijper'', p. 37.</ref> one of four unused copies known in private collections and museums.<ref name=Reuters/><ref>''[https://www.knbf.nl/uploads/pdf/nieuwsbrieven/043%20Nieuwsbrief%20november%202013.pdf Nieuwsbrief]'', KNBF, Vol. 4, No. 43, 15 November 2013, p. 8.</ref> Another rare item was a 1925 unused Ceylon 1000R (SG323) plate number single with a certificate by Friedl.<ref>''The Collection Aat de Peijper'', p. 21.</ref> Both were formerly in the Samos collection. The de Peijper collection was auctioned by De Nederlandsche Postzegelveiling in 2013, with the £100 Kenya and Uganda stamp reckoned to be the most valuable stamp ever to be auctioned in the Netherlands.<ref name=Reuters>[https://www.reuters.com/article/npv-idUSnBw255497a+100+BSW20131025 Rare British Commonwealth Stamp to Be Auctioned at Dutch Auction House NPV.] [[Reuters]], 25 October 2013. Retrieved 26 March 2016.</ref><ref>[http://www.trouw.nl/tr/nl/4324/Nieuws/article/detail/3532535/2013/10/24/Duurste-postzegel-ooit-in-Nederland-geveild.dhtml Duurste postzegel ooit in Nederland geveild.] ''deVerdieping Trouw'', 24 October 2013. Retrieved 26 March 2016.</ref>
==Stamps of the de Peijper collection== <gallery> File:East Africa & Uganda Protectorates 1912 500R.jpg|1912, East Africa & Uganda Protectorates, 500R. Formerly in the Samos collection.<ref>''The Collection Aat de Peijper'', p. 17.</ref> File:1925 Ceylon 1000R (SG323) plate number single.jpg|1925, Ceylon 1000R plate number single. File:Kenya & Uganda £100 SG105.jpg|1925, Kenya & Uganda £100 plate number single. </gallery>
