{{one source|date=May 2010}} {{Infobox University | name = Baltimore International College | motto = | established = 1972 | defunct = 2011 | type = [[Private university|Private]] | city = [[Baltimore, Maryland|Baltimore]] | state = [[Maryland]] | country = [[United States]] | total = 800 <ref name="bic.edu"/> | coor = {{coord|39|17|17|N|76|36|0|W|region:US-MD_type:edu|display=inline,title}} | campus = 2 locations ([[Baltimore, Maryland]], [[Virginia, County Cavan|Virginia, Ireland]])<ref name="bic.edu"/> | website = [http://www.bic.edu/ http://www.bic.edu/] }}
The '''Baltimore International College (BIC)''', founded in 1972, was a [[Private university|private]], [[Non-profit organization|non-profit]] college located in [[Baltimore, Maryland]]. It offered specialized degree programs in [[Culinary Arts]] and [[Hospitality management studies|Hospitality Management]].<ref name="bic.edu">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bic.edu/displayProspective.asp?keywords=AboutBIC |title=Baltimore International College: About BIC |access-date=2008-09-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080804004228/http://www.bic.edu/displayProspective.asp?keywords=AboutBIC |archive-date=2008-08-04 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> The College was taken over by [[Stratford University]] in January 2012.
==History== BIC was accredited by the [[American Culinary Federation]]. It lost its accreditation from the [[Middle States Association of Colleges and Schools]] on August 31, 2011 due to unaddressed issues from its 2007 review.<ref>[http://www.baltimoresun.com/news/maryland/bs-md-baltimore-international-accredi20110628,0,5018763.story Baltimore Sun: Baltimore International College to lose accreditation in August]</ref> BIC was acquired by [[Stratford University]] in January 2012, and the former campuses are now Stratford campuses.
==Campus & facilities== The college’s main campus is located in [[downtown Baltimore]] near the [[Inner Harbor]]. The college owns two full-service hotels [[downtown Baltimore]]—the [http://www.mountvernonbaltimore.com/ Mount Vernon Hotel] and [http://www.hopkinsinnbaltimore.com/ Hopkins Inn]. Further, BIC owns and operates the Bay Atlantic Club, which offers delivery breakfast and lunch, dine-in lunch, and as banquet hall with reservations.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://bic.edu/displayContent.asp?keywords=BAC |title=Baltimore International College: The Bay Atlantic Club |access-date=2008-09-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080907031502/http://bic.edu/displayContent.asp?Keywords=BAC |archive-date=2008-09-07 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> In addition, the college operates the [http://www.parkhotelvirginia.com/ Park Hotel] on its 100-acre (400,000 m²) Virginia Park satellite campus in [[Virginia, County Cavan|Virginia]], [[County Cavan]], [[Ireland]].<ref name="bic.edu"/>
==Students== The college offers student housing in Dublin Hall, which is location in the Mount Vernon Hotel.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bic.edu/displayProspective.asp?keywords=StudentHousing |title=Baltimore International College: Student Housing and Dining |access-date=2008-09-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081025021950/http://www.bic.edu/displayProspective.asp?keywords=StudentHousing |archive-date=2008-10-25 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> Slightly more than half (52 percent) of its 800 or so students are male.<ref name="bic.edu"/>
