{{Infobox NRHP | name = McGavock Family Cemetery | nrhp_type = | designated_other1 = Virginia Landmarks Register | designated_other1_date = March 20, 1979<ref name=register>{{cite web|title=Virginia Landmarks Register|url=http://www.dhr.virginia.gov/registers/register_counties_cities.htm|publisher=Virginia Department of Historic Resources|accessdate=5 June 2013}}</ref> | designated_other1_number = 098-0022 | designated_other1_num_position = bottom | image = McGavock Family Cemetery.jpg | caption = | location = NW of Rural Retreat, near [[Fort Chiswell, Virginia]] | coordinates = {{coord|36|56|51|N|80|55|30|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Virginia#USA | built = {{Start date|1812}} | builder = Krone, Laurence | architecture = Germanic | added = June 22, 1979 | area = less than one acre | governing_body = Private | refnum = 79003098<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }} '''McGavock Family Cemetery''' is a historic family [[cemetery]] located near [[Fort Chiswell, Virginia|Fort Chiswell]], [[Wythe County, Virginia]]. It is located on a hill above [[The Mansion at Fort Chiswell]]. The cemetery includes approximately about 15 Germanic [[sandstone]] monuments dating from 1812 to the late-1830s.<ref name=VAnom>{{cite web|url=http://www.dhr.virginia.gov/registers/Counties/Wythe/098-0022_McGavock_Family_Cemetery_1979_Final_Nomination.pdf|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: McGavock Family Cemetery |author=Virginia Historic Landmarks Commission Staff|date=February 1979 |publisher=Virginia Department of Historic Resources}} and [http://www.dhr.virginia.gov/registers/Counties/Wythe/KimberlingLutheranChurch_photo.htm ''Accompanying photo'']</ref>
It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1980.<ref name=nris/>
